Use **`WebApplicationFactory<TEntryPoint>`** from `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.Testing`. It hosts your app in-memory and gives you an `HttpClient` — no port, no real server.

### Setup

```bash
dotnet add tests/MyMcp.Tests package Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.Testing
```

### Example test

```csharp
public class McpIntegrationTests : IClassFixture<WebApplicationFactory<Program>>
{
    private readonly HttpClient _client;

    public McpIntegrationTests(WebApplicationFactory<Program> factory)
    {
        _client = factory.CreateClient();
    }

    [Fact]
    public async Task Initialize_ReturnsCapabilities()
    {
        var request = new
        {
            jsonrpc = "2.0",
            id = 1,
            method = "initialize",
            @params = new
            {
                protocolVersion = "2025-03-26",
                capabilities = new { },
                clientInfo = new { name = "test-client", version = "1.0" }
            }
        };

        var response = await _client.PostAsJsonAsync("/mcp", request);

        response.EnsureSuccessStatusCode();
        var body = await response.Content.ReadFromJsonAsync<JsonElement>();
        Assert.Equal("2025-03-26",
            body.GetProperty("result")
                .GetProperty("protocolVersion")
                .GetString());
    }

    [Fact]
    public async Task ToolsList_ReturnsRegisteredTools()
    {
        // Initialize first (required by MCP protocol)
        await InitializeSession();

        var request = new { jsonrpc = "2.0", id = 2, method = "tools/list" };
        var response = await _client.PostAsJsonAsync("/mcp", request);

        response.EnsureSuccessStatusCode();
        var body = await response.Content.ReadFromJsonAsync<JsonElement>();
        var tools = body.GetProperty("result").GetProperty("tools");
        Assert.True(tools.GetArrayLength() > 0);
    }
}
```

### Key points

| Concern | Approach |
|---|---|
| **No real server** | `WebApplicationFactory` hosts in-process via `TestServer` |
| **Override services** | Use `factory.WithWebHostBuilder(b => b.ConfigureServices(...))` to swap dependencies (e.g., mock databases) |
| **Session/state** | If your MCP server uses sessions, create a dedicated `HttpClient` per test or share one with `InitializeSession()` |
| **SSE transport** | Use `factory.CreateClient()` + `HttpClient.GetStreamAsync()` to consume the SSE stream |
| **Ensure `Program` is visible** | Add `<InternalsVisibleTo Include="MyMcp.Tests" />` or a `public partial class Program { }` marker |

This gives you real HTTP semantics (headers, content negotiation, middleware pipeline) with in-process speed.
